# Resume Tailor Pro

An AI-powered resume tailoring studio. It uses your **master resume as the single
source of truth** and rewrites, reorganizes, and emphasizes your real experience
for a target job — **without ever fabricating** companies, projects, dates, skills,
or achievements. Output is an editable resume plus print-ready PDF / DOCX / HTML / JSON.

> Starts empty — **import your own resume** (PDF/DOCX/paste) and it becomes the master. No preset personal data.

## Run it

```bash
npm install      # already done
npm run dev      # http://localhost:5175  (app + /api/gemini proxy)
```

Production: `npm run build && npm start` → http://localhost:4173 (serves `dist/` + proxy).
Other scripts: `npm run typecheck`.

AI is optional — without a `.env` key the app runs fully on local heuristics. To enable
Gemini, put your key in `.env` (see `.env.example`) and restart.

## What's inside

| Area | Feature |
| --- | --- |
| **Dashboard** | Live ATS & job-match scores, section coverage, version history, quick actions, mini preview |
| **Editor** | Edit every section, contact & links, section reorder, design controls (accent, font size, line height, spacing, bullet style, headings), undo/redo, reset-to-master, save versions |
| **Templates** | 5 distinct layouts — **Classic · Modern · Minimal · Executive · Bold** — live thumbnails + full-screen preview. Colors/fonts/spacing are adjustable in the editor |
| **AI Studio** | Tailor Resume · Improve Wording · Rewrite Summary · ATS Optimize · Condense · Expand · Job Match score (strong/missing/weak/suggestions) · Keyword analysis (green = present, red = gap) · Cover Letter / Email / LinkedIn note |
| **Export** | Print-ready PDF, editable DOCX (Word/Docs), standalone HTML, JSON data |

## How the AI works

Two layers:

1. **Local heuristics** (`src/lib/ai.ts`) — keyword extraction, job matching, ATS
   scoring, tailoring, and drafts run instantly in the browser with **no key**.
2. **Gemini** (optional, higher quality) — Tailor / Improve / Rewrite Summary /
   ATS Optimize / Cover Letter call Google Gemini. If Gemini errors, they
   **automatically fall back** to the local heuristics.

### Gemini is server-side — the key never reaches the browser

The API key lives only in `.env` on the server. The browser calls a local
`/api/gemini` proxy (`server/gemini.mjs`), which injects the key and forwards to
Google. The end user never sees, enters, or manages a key.

```
# .env  (git-ignored, server-only — never prefixed with VITE_)
GEMINI_API_KEY=your-key
GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash
```

- **Dev:** the proxy is a Vite middleware plugin (`server/vitePlugin.mjs`), so
  `npm run dev` serves both the app and `/api/gemini`.
- **Prod:** `npm run build && npm start` runs `server/prod.mjs`, which serves
  `dist/` plus the proxy.

The AI Studio shows a status badge (configured / off / not-configured) and a
toggle to opt out — but no key field. Every prompt enforces a strict
"never fabricate" rule, so the model only rephrases and reorders real content.

## Tech

Vite · React 18 · TypeScript · Tailwind v4 · Zustand (with `localStorage` persistence)
· lucide-react. Templates are a single config-driven renderer (`src/templates/`) with
five layout families: classic, modern, minimal, bold, and two-column sidebar.

## Structure

```
src/
  data/masterResume.ts        # empty resume + shared section defaults + isResumeEmpty()
  types.ts                    # resume + template + analysis models
  store/useResumeStore.ts     # Zustand: working copy, versions, undo/redo, design
  lib/ai.ts, keywords.ts      # tailoring, ATS, match, keywords, cover letters
  lib/export.ts               # PDF (print) / DOCX / HTML / JSON
  templates/registry.ts       # 5 templates (Classic/Modern/Minimal/Executive/Bold)
  templates/ResumeTemplate.tsx# config-driven layout engine
  components/                 # Dashboard, Editor, TemplateBrowser, AIStudio, ExportPanel, PreviewPane
```
